This was our first time trying Vapianos, we are honestly a little underwhelmed. The ordering process is very odd. It’s a mix between a restaurant and a fast-casual place. I tipped my tab but honestly I’m not sure who it goes to.  We were told everything was made fresh in front of us which led us to believe that we were supposed to wait in the front for our food to be made but since everything is made to order we realized it was gonna take a while. And boy it did... Took over 30min for a pizza and a calzone. There wasn’t anywhere that indicated where to place the buzzer either when picking up our food. Just a small box in the front without any signage.  Pizza was good, calzone was okay. Not hot, barely warm. The area that has all seasoning didn’t have Parmesan cheese unfortunately.  Ordered a drink but the freestyle machine was doing a maintenance routine so half the drinks were unavailable.  We also had ordered garlic bread, somehow that was never made. The lady said she could quickly make them and we could come back down to get them, we had already waited a while and weren’t about to go back and forth between upstairs and downstairs. She didn’t offer to bring them up either. We ordered desserts and those were really good, although a little pricey. $10 for 2 mousse.  We would consider going back to try something different but probably at another location.

Interesting concept as far as ordering and paying, but it doesn’t seem to work well in practice. You order directly at a chef station, and they give you a table number. Then runners bring your food out.  One of our entrees came out, and we pointed out to the runner that we still needed the 2nd entree so he left our table number. 20 mins later I still haven’t gotten my food. Since you don’t have an assigned waiter, I didn’t even know who to ask. I asked 2 different runners and neither ever came back. After about an hour there in total we had to leave so we just went down to the front desk and told her what happened and to just cancel my entree. She asked the chef and it seemed like he had just forgotten it or something, but it also seemed like nobody knew I had been asking people where my food was for the last 20 minutes.  They cancelled the one entree we didn’t get from the bill, but didn’t offer to do anything else. I ended up eating Jimmy Johns in the car on the way home instead. What a nice date night. This was one of our favorite places to eat on our week long Chicago trip.  I had saved it to a very long google list of restaurants that had good reviews and we just happened to be close by one night we were hungry.  It’s such a cool concept to get a card when you walk in, go to all the stations you want food from (huge selection), and then just pay for what’s on the card at the very end of your dining experience.  The atmosphere is really chill, comfortable, and inviting.  The only issue I had is that I wasn’t smart enough to work their complimentary phone chargers (lol...ugh!).  The food was excellent.  My wife and I split a salad and a pasta dish and had plenty to eat.  We ate upstairs close to the bar and both had a couple of drinks that were both great.  I REALLY wish we had one of these places where we live.  We’d eat there weekly, guaranteed.
